In sn12 usecase it's a validator (each validator to be exact). The miners deposit to contracts of validators (in exchange valis give organic jobs to them, organics give better incentive) and when a validator discovers unwanted behaviour they can slash / burn the collateral in this validator contract of the offending miner.
so for n validators you need to make n deposits ?
how much would these deposits be?
it the deposit amount is static , after a while they can exploit it if the profit is more than the collateral lost

In sn12 we didn't decide yet, we were discussing 10tao for starters.

Yes, that's why we figure it is better not to require a fixed amount deposit, but to prioritize the miners based on the amount they deposited... So the more a miner deposits, the more organic traffic they get, the more incentives they can pull:)
